#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MemoryStrategiesHTGThreshold.md:1
msgid ""
"`vtkHyperTreeGridThreshold` now supports multiple strategies for "
"representing its output in memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MemoryStrategiesHTGThreshold.md:3
msgid ""
"The `vtkHyperTreeGridThreshold` now exposes a `SetMemoryStrategy` method for "
"choosing the structure of its output in memory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MemoryStrategiesHTGThreshold.md:4
msgid ""
"`MaskInput` (=0, default): shallow copy and mask the input to describe the "
"threshold"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MemoryStrategiesHTGThreshold.md:5
msgid ""
"`CopyStructureAndIndexArrays` (=1): generate an new HTG in the output with "
"cell arrays indexed on the output using `vtkIndexedArray`s"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MemoryStrategiesHTGThreshold.md:6
msgid ""
"`DeepThreshold` (=2): generate a completely new HTG describing the threshold "
"of the input from scratch"
msgstr ""
